President Obama announced the nomination of several individuals for key administration posts. David C. Gompert was nominated for Principal Deputy National Intelligence Director, William E. Kennard was nominated as Representative of the United States of America to the European Union, Alan D. Solomont was nominated as Ambassador to Spain and Andorra, and Robert J. Grey, John G. Levi, Martha L. Minow, Julie A. Reiskin, and Gloria Valencia-Weber were nominated as Board Members of the Legal Services Corporation. Additionally, Ruth Y. Goldway was announced as the new Chair of the Postal Regulatory Commission. President Obama expressed his confidence in these individuals and their ability to contribute to his administration's work in strengthening the nation.